---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy & Terms — Animate Stock"
  description="Privacy policy and terms of use for the Animate Stock iPhone app and animatestock.com."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy &amp; Terms of Use</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: June 11, 2026</em></p>
    <p>
      This page describes how Animate Stock (the iOS app) and animatestock.com
      (the website), operated by Applorium, handle your information, and the
      terms that apply when you use the app.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

    <h3>What the app collects</h3>
    <p>
      Animate Stock does not require an account and does not collect personal
      information. Your projects, custom events, and exported videos are stored
      locally on your device.
    </p>

    <h3>Market data requests</h3>
    <p>
      When you search for a ticker or load price history, the app requests data
      from third-party market data providers. These requests include the ticker
      symbol and date range but no personal identifiers beyond what any internet
      request technically includes (such as your IP address, handled by the
      provider under their own policies).
    </p>

    <h3>Company logos</h3>
    <p>
      Ticker logos shown in the app are fetched from a third-party logo service.
      These requests include only the ticker symbol. Fetched logos are cached on
      your device.
    </p>

    <h3>In-app purchases</h3>
    <p>
      Payments are processed by Apple through the App Store; we never see your
      payment details. To unlock purchases across reinstalls and devices, the
      app uses <a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy">RevenueCat</a>, which
      receives an anonymous app-generated identifier and your purchase history.
      RevenueCat does not receive your name, email, or Apple ID.
    </p>

    <h3>Photos access</h3>
    <p>
      If you choose to save an exported video, the app asks for
      permission to add it to your photo library. The app only writes the files
      you export; it does not read your existing photos.
    </p>

    <h3>The website</h3>
    <p>
      animatestock.com is a static website. It does not set cookies and does not
      run third-party trackers.
    </p>

    <h3>Changes</h3>
    <p>
      If this policy changes, the updated version will be posted on this page
      with a new "last updated" date.
    </p>

    <h2>Terms of Use</h2>

    <h3>Using the app</h3>
    <p>
      Animate Stock is licensed to you for personal use under Apple's standard
      <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/itunes/dev/stdeula/">
      Licensed Application End User License Agreement</a>. The videos and GIFs
      you export are yours to keep and share.
    </p>

    <h3>Subscriptions and purchases</h3>
    <p>
      Some features require a Pro upgrade, available as an auto-renewing
      subscription or one-time purchase. Subscriptions renew automatically
      unless cancelled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.
      You can manage or cancel them anytime in your App Store account settings,
      and restore previous purchases from the app's Settings tab. Refunds are
      handled by Apple.
    </p>

    <h3>Market data accuracy</h3>
    <p>
      Charts are built from third-party market data, which can contain errors,
      gaps, or delays. Some values — such as historical market caps and
      what-if investment scenarios — are estimates derived from that data.
      Animate Stock makes no guarantee that any figure shown is accurate or
      complete.
    </p>

    <h3>Not financial advice</h3>
    <p>
      Animate Stock visualizes historical market data for informational and
      entertainment purposes only. Nothing in the app is financial, investment,
      or trading advice, and past performance does not predict future results.
    </p>

    <h3>Limitation of liability</h3>
    <p>
      The app is provided "as is", without warranties of any kind. To the
      maximum extent permitted by law, Applorium is not liable for any damages
      arising from your use of the app, including decisions made based on the
      data it displays.
    </p>

    <h3>Changes to these terms</h3>
    <p>
      We may update these terms as the app evolves. Continued use of the app
      after an update means you accept the revised terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions? Email <a href="mailto:apps@applorium.com">apps@applorium.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
